This executive order, issued by President Donald Trump on September 27, 2019, continues the existence of various advisory committees until September 30, 2021. These committees include the Committee for the Preservation of the White House, the President's Commission on White House Fellowships, the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, the President's Export Council, and others. The order also designates the heads of the respective departments or agencies to perform the functions of the President under the Federal Advisory Committee Act for these committees. Sections 1 and 2 of a previous executive order are superseded by this order, and it takes effect on September 30, 2019.